<Author>SEG1Wales
<Content>Pricey. Stayed here for 6 nights as part of a 2 week vacation in the USA.We chose this hotel as we were hiring a car and were uncertain about the parking in downtown Boston.Parking at 32 dollars / day was, we felt very expensive especially as we were staying at the hotel for a week-no reduction.Hotel itself was pleasant with clean and nicely decorated rooms.Toiletries and fresh towels were provided daily.We had interconnecting harbourview rooms with lovely views of Boston harbour.Hotel however very inconvenient to downtown Boston-either an expensive water taxi fare or a free shuttle bus service to the T terminal,stopping at all the airline terminals on route!.We ate on our last night at the hotel s restautant - O.K. but would not rave about the food.This hotel as previously mentioned hosts many weddings.On our last night,we were kept awake for 3 hours by a very noisy wedding party-loud music,drinking,talking,laughing etc which was continuing in the room next door to ours (1a.m.-4a.m.).We did not appreciate this as we had a 5 a.m.start the next day and 3 young children in bed-aged 9,8 and 5 years.This is not something we expected in an airport hotel with people arriving and leaving at all hours of the day and night.We did complain to reception at the time about the matter and the general manager was sent to the room next door to sort things out.My husband overheard the conversation and on opening our bedroom door saw the occupant next door handing the manager money and asking him to FIX IT for them to carry on with the party.( MONEY ACCEPTED).Following my husband s protest re early start, young children in the room etc,the party was moved to a room further along the corridor !!!!!.Again this is not something you would expect nor is acceptable in such a hotel.It spoilt our stay. 
