<Author>gonzaleyes
<Content>DIFFERENT VIEW OF BOSTON Stayed at the Hyatt 4 nights. Not sure if it's a 4 star, but it's close. Let's go 3-1/2 to be safe. Room was comfortable, clean and fairly large. Bed and pillows were super! Bathroom was OK...clean but in need of an update and re-grouting. Has a business center but WOW..crazy expensive. Great views both sides. Fun glass elevator. Really close to the Airport with free shuttle which is nice if you have an early or late flight. In hind sight I would have spent my last day there for the convenience of the airport but in town the rest of my stay. There is NOTHING around the hotel. The water taxi into town is spendy everyday. $17 (plus tip) round trip so you kind of have to add that on to you nightly stay. And if you have to do it twice it's a bummer. The Harborside Grill at the hotel is good but pretty spendy as well. Although it has a great kids menu and the adult portions are huge. You can share a meal easily. All in all it was a pleasent experience and would absolutly stay there again.... especially on my last night in Boston. 
