<Content>A Good Place to Stay This is a good hotel located at Logan Airport. However, you should only stay at this hotel if you are flying out the next day. It is too expensive to take a taxi back and forth into Boston.The hotel is good and the staff is wonderful. I can't fault the service. However, there are some annoying problems. First, there are no safes in the rooms. Even lower rated hotels have in-room safes. Second, the housekeeping is a hit and miss thing. Sometimes there are no wash clothes, other times no face towels. Sometimes there is no shampoo, other times no conditioner or bath soap. It is as if there is no check list of what should be in the bathroom. I know these are small problems but they can be annoying when you arrive late at night and are tired.The view from the harbor rooms are spectacular. It is worth the extra money to have that view. The restaurants are expensive but good. Room service is prompt and really expensive. One problem the hotel does have , is the noise in the hallways. Doors are constantly slamming, dogs bark all the time and kids run up and down the halls. I know the hotel can't control this but it does make sleeping difficult. I would stay here again if I were flying in and out of Boston, but one night is enough. This is not a hotel for a long term stay. Too far from the city of Boston and all its atractions. 
