<Content>My place to stay at Logan! I'm originally from Boston and have stayed at many of the Logan hotels due to early and/or late flights. The Hyatt is definitely the best of the bunch. As many of the other reviews mention, the views are excellent. This past time I had a view of the runway, and its really cool (and quiet). Who would believe that?My only complaint is the parking fee. $32 a night? I still had my rental car, and was looking forward to leaving my huge suitcase in there, and pulling out only what I needed, and returning the car in the morning. $32 seemed a bit steep for the 6 hours that I was going to be there, so I had to return the car to Hertz, take a Hertz shuttle to terminal A, and then the Hyatt shuttle. It was after midnight, so I didn't have my wits about me, but what I should have done was call the Hyatt for a pick up at Hertz.The best part is that I always make my reservation for this through Priceline, and get great deals. If you need to be at Logan, I would highly recommend this hotel. Heck, I would recommend it to tourists as well, as long as you don't mind being a bit out of the way. 
