<Content>Amazing water views We just returned from an amazing stay at the Hyatt Harborside in Boston. It was an excellent experience and I highly recommend it. We shopped around for prices and they were competitive with hotels that did not offer 1/3 in amenities, service, etc. Very luxurious surroundings and gorgeous views from the moment you arrive welcome you from the moment you arrive. The gorgeous views from a large picture window continued in our room and we did not even stay in a suite. The service was excellent and the best part is that they are five minutes from the airport via the hotel shuttle. They have an outdoor patio looking at the Boston skyline/harbor that takes your breath away as you have a wonderful and complete breakfast buffet, cocktails or dinner. Anytime during your stay you can hop on the water taxi and it will take you across the harbor to downtown boston in less than 10 minutes. We received free tickets during our stay but if it is not included in your package you can purchase them from the front desk for $14.00. They will drop you off at various locations, ie., Aquarium, Fanuel Hall, etc. This was a great stay and I highly recommend this hotel in Boston. 
