<Author>jbcoach
<Content>Loved this hotel I cannot say enough good things about this hotel. We just finished a 2-week, 14-day stay through the East Coast and stayed in some of the top hotels on the East Coast, and I can honestly tell you that this hotel was as good as each hotel, maybe more, at a fraction of the cost. I booked this trip on a deal I saw on travelzoo for an incredible $129 per night......a steal compared to rates I was quoted from the hotel directly. We were concerned because of the location of this hotel, but that vanished quickly when we saw the view the Harborside gave us of downtown Boston. It was simply stunning. We hung out at the hotel restaurant, which was very good. We stayed outside on lounge chairs and had a great time. The kids loved the pool. The service was incredible. We were greeted warmly by an incredible bellman, who helped us with everything. The front desk staff was very nice, and helped us with any questions we had. We didn't have one problem. Our only regret is that we didn't stay longer than the original 3 days we had planned. IT WAS THAT GOOD! Honestly, we stayed at the Sofitel in Philly, and this hotel was better. The rooms were clean and roomy. The beds were incredibly comfortable, and the staff was friendly and helpful. The Clam Chowder on at the restaurant was as good as any we had on our trip, and believe me, we had alot. I would recommend this hotel to anyone looking for a great place to stay in Boston. It is a quick trip by taxi, or even more fun, by water taxi, to downtown Boston. This is a great hotel, with great people, great food, and a great location......as long as you aren't too hung up on being directly downtown. We loved it!! 
