<Author>Greylady
<Content>Room with a view at the Hyatt Harborside We stayed at the Hyatt Harborside on both ends of a trip to Costa Rica, as we had an early a.m. flight out of Logan on the way down and a very late p.m. flight on the way back. We booked through Priceline, so weren't sure what kind of room we'd be in, but were more than pleasantly surprised given the rate we got. The night before we left, we had an 11th floor harbor side view of the city that was incredible. On the return we were upgraded from the room we had booked to a 3rd floor harbor view that was not as impressive as the 11th floor, but still better than any airport hotel we've ever stayed at (besides, at 1:30 a.m. you don't much care if you have a view, and in the morning you're busy getting ready to leave). In both cases the rooms were good- size, clean, the beds were very comfortable and had all the amenities (the only thing that didn't work was the iron in the 1st room). We agree with other reviewers about the staff - exceptionally friendly, professional and helpful. However, we had an entirely different experience with the shuttle service than most of the other reviews we read. It was prompt, the drivers were friendly and knowledgeable - one even gave us all a little tour-guide routine along the way, and explained the hotel's amenities as well. We'd also have to agree with the reviews of the restaurant. Extremely overpriced, and no other option on site. We ordered room service off the bar menu (speedy, friendly staff, not gourmet food, but good) and dined in front of the picture window looking out over the harbor at the twinkling lights of the city. It was a great start to our vacation! We wouldn't hesitate to return and have already recommended to others planning to do the Logan shuffle. 
