<Content>Ok, but.... We stayed here for our anniversary visit to Boston. The hotel is clean and staff is polite. The location is a fine alternative to the generally more pricey downtown hotels. The hotel provides a free shuttle service to/from the airport and the nearby underground/subway station. Unfortunately, there were several occurances including our initial pickup from the airport where the communications between driver and hotel dispatcher were very slow or non existent resulting in long delays while waiting for this pickup. We weren't the only ones finding this misfortune...one fellow waited for over 1 hour at the airport car hire office and after two calls to the hotel was finally picked up by the shuttle we were on. The driver told him no one had told him someone was waiting. Thus, you must build in much more time than necessary to your schedule for travel to and from downtown, the airport, etc. Also, the whirlpool hot tub although very clean would not run...only very hot standing water. The hotel only offers one very highly priced restaurant. It has great views but considering the isolated location of the hotel adjacent to the airport, they have a captive audience and we felt taken advantage of. Apparently in former perhaps more prosperous times, there was an additional dining room option. Suggestion: We brought in tasty hand made pastries and fruit from Boston's 'little Italy' the night before for the next morning's breakfast. There is complementary room coffee and tea. Generally, I'd say, stay here understanding there might be some glitches and if the price appears lower than some other nearby options. 
