<Content>Mixed review for Hyatt Harborside My husband, son and I stayed at the Harborside when we took our son to Boston for freshman orientation. Here are the positives and negatives, as I saw them, broken down:Positive:1.) Nice facility with a beautiful view if you're lucky enough to face the city.2.) Harborside grill had good food, a lovely view and very reasonable prices for LUNCH.3.) Very nice workout room and sauna. 4.) Great access to Logan Airport. Shuttle buses run a continuous circuit throughout the day.5.) Great access to the T metro trains. Hotel shuttle bus will drop you off at the airport metro station after dropping off guests with departing flights. The T is a bargain and it will get you into the city quickly.6.) Room was nicely decorated and clean.Negative:1.) My husband believes that the bed in our room was the most uncomfortable he's ever slept on - and he's been deployed overseas with the Army!2.) Not knowing any better, we booked through Priceline auction and still overpaid. I forgot to check the better bidding message boards before placing my bid. bad...bad....bad...3.) Although we paid less than the published room rate, we still paid 100% more than we should have on the auction bid, according to the bidding message boards. Nonetheless, we feel that we were given a substandard room (overlooked the airport, two EXTREMELY small, uncomfortable double beds - they were more like twin beds plus).4.) Parking is very expensive - $22.00/day, but that's supposedly okay for Boston.5.) The noise level in our room was ridiculous. I agree with the person that earlier reported about the thin walls and slamming doors. 6.) The pool area is pretty (it overlooks the harbor and city), but the pool itself is very small AND COLD. It is an indoor pool and we were there at the end of AUGUST.7.) Prices for dinner at either restaurant were very high. Room service? Ouch.8.) There is nothing close-by except the airport.9.) Attitude of the front desk staff could have been better. We didn't have any issues with them - they were just naturally standoffish.Overall...I'm just somewhere in the middle about rating this hotel. Too bad, it sits at a beautiful location and has the potential to be something special. 
