<Content>Nice View but that's All THE GOOD.... View from your room, either side. Harbor side gives great view of Boston Harbor and skyline, but it's always the same. We had the Airport View, where you can watch planes land and take off constantly, but no jet noise. I prefered the Logan view, but that's just me. Also the shuttle service was consistent and good, espcially to the airport subway stop.THE BAD.... I was told they had a business center so didn't bring laptop. I wasn't told business center is closed from Friday afternoon to Monday morning.And it cost $10 for 15 minutes on internet. OK it's Boston, but geez!!Except for one over-worked waitress, the downstairs restaurant had mediocre food and HORRIBLE service. Rude, no smiles, beg for your drink refills, find your own menu, only had two waitstaff on a Saturday night in August. You're in one of the great food cities of the world, don't eat hotel food (I told myself later).Convenient to airport, sure, but did you go to visit the airport. If you have a car (cost $22/day to park) you can drive yourself into town (pay toll and $12 to park). If you are car-less (best way to be), you have to shuttle to subway and subway to town. Subway is great and easy but I'd rather walk out of my hotel and alredy be in the center of it all.So if you just want a room with a view, this is your hotel... otherwise no. 
